title: Grateful Dead Live at Olympia Halle on 1974-09-14
description:
Set 1

Bertha, Me & My Uncle, Deal, Jack Straw, Scarlet Begonias, Promised Land, Loser, El Paso, Row Jimmy, Weather Report Suite Prelude-> Weather Report Suite Part 1-> Let It Grow, Tennessee Jed, Around & Around

Set 2

Phil & Ned*, Big River, Sugaree, Mexicali Blues, Mississippi Half Step-> It Must Have Been The Roses, Truckin'-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, Eyes Of The World-> One More Saturday Night, E: U.S. Blues

*Phil & Ned Between sets.

reviews.review_text:
Eyes!!! First few songs are AUD, which is somewhat boomy sounding.  This matrix as a whole is fairly well done, with good patching where one source has drop-outs.  Keyboards are pretty high in the mix, not a bad thing.

There is a nice, short MLB at the end of Truckin'.  The Eyes is fantastic.

Excellent Matrix and Show! 10/10, excellent show, splendid mixing, grand performances, perfect era, exceptional set list, you can hear the soundboard AND the audience, I’m listening to this while reading the Deadbase 50 entry on a dose w/ some K and Chocolope. It’s groovy synchronistic night. I wish more people commented while on their aural psychedelia timetravelling listening journeys. Much love for this show and all of ‘74. 

Love is Real NFA (~);} 2404
